STEP 1: Create Resource Group
- Navigate to Azure Portal/ Resource Groups/ Create
- Name: "rg_Soc_lab
- Region: Same region for all resources

STEP 2: Create Virtual Network and Subnet
- Navigate to Virtual Networks/ Create
- VNet Name: vn_soc_lab

STEP 3: Create Network Security Group (NSG)
- Navigate to Network Security Groups/ Create
- Name: "Vm-soc-lab-nsg
- Add inbound rules:
  - Allow RDP from my IP only
  - Explicit deny all other inbound traffic
-Add outbound rules:
  - Allow HTTPS outbound
  - Explicit deny all other outbound traffic
- Attach NSG to "Subnet-Soc"

STEP 4: Create Virtual MAchine
- Navigate to Cirtual Machine/ Create
- Name: VM_soc_lab
- OS: Windows
- Networking:
  - Virtual Network: vn_soc_lab
  - Subnet: "Subnet-Soc"
- Disable any public inbound ports outside NSG

STEP 5: Enable Virtual Network Flow Logs
-Navigate to Azure Portal/ Network Watcher/ Logs/ FLow logs
- Enable Virtual Network
- Create Storage account
- Retention (30 Days)
- Save








